        <h6 class="section-name">PRIVACY</h6>
        <div class="info">
          Effective Date: May 7th, 2013
          <br>
          <br>
          This Privacy Policy describes Talamu, Inc.’s (hereinafter “Unlockable,” “we” or “us”) privacy policy, including the types of information we gather, how we use it, with whom the information may be shared, what choices are available to you regarding collection, use and distribution of information and our efforts to protect the information you provide to us through our website at  <a href='http://unlockable.com' class="info-text-link">Unlockable.com</a> (the “Website”), through our computing applications, our software integrated into the websites and services of others, and through other services delivered or provided to you by Unlockable (collectively, the “Service”). By using the Service, you hereby consent to allow us to process information in accordance with this Policy. Please also refer to our <a href="#terms-conditions" class="info-text-link">Terms of Use</a>, which are incorporated as if fully recited herein, if you have not already done so.
          <br>
          <br>
          This policy is subject to change. If our information retention or usage practices change, we will let you know by posting the Privacy Policy changes on the Website or otherwise through the Service. Please refer to the “Effective Date” above to see when this Policy was last updated.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Territoriality</span>
          <br>
          Regardless of where our servers are located, your personal data will be processed by us in the United States, where data protection and privacy regulations may or may not be to the same level of protection as in other parts of the world. BY VISITING THE SERVICE, YOU UNEQUIVOCALLY AND UNAMBIGUOUSLY CONSENT TO THE COLLECTION AND PROCESSING IN THE UNITED STATES OF ANY INFORMATION COLLECTED OR OBTAINED BY US THROUGH VOLUNTARY SUBMISSIONS, AND THAT U.S. LAW GOVERNS ANY SUCH COLLECTION AND PROCESSING.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Information Collected</span>
          <br>
          We collect two types of information about persons who use the Service: personal information and non-personal information. This information may be collected in a number of ways, including through direct submission, cookies, web beacons and similar data acquisition methods. Although you can disable cookies in your browser or device, they will interfere with the use of the Service.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Personal Information Collected</span>
          <br>
          Personal information is information that would permit us to contact you, or serves as a persistent identifier of you within Unlockable.
          <br>
          Personal Information that we may collect includes:
          <p class="info-text-indent">
            • Name;<br>
            • Address;<br>
            • E-mail;<br>
            • Username;<br>
            • IP address;<br>
            • Device identifier (e.g., IMEI);<br>
            • Location based information;<br></p>
          <br>
          Unlockable does not collect any Personal Information about you without your voluntary consent. This information may be supplied to Unlockable when you sign-up for the Service, when you complete a survey, when you create or update an account, when you request services or otherwise when you explicitly submit it. In addition, if you integrate your use of the Service with social media, such as Facebook or LinkedIn, Unlockable may collect Personal Information about you from those sources. This information may be supplemented through third-party database vendors.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Non-Personal Information</span>
          <br>
          Non-Personal Information is information about you, other than Personal Information, that may be collected by Unlockable. It may include non-personal information about how you use the Service, such as browsing habits, information about the referring source of your traffic, your anonymous demographic details, your interactions with the Service and analytics relating to your use of the Service. If you request, the Service may include accessing other data on your device, such as your contacts and calendar, for the purpose of fulfilling specific requests.
          <br>
          <br>
          If you integrate your use of the Service with social media, such as Facebook or LinkedIn, Unlockable may collect additional information about you from those sources, such as self-reported data, interests and social connections. This information may be supplemented through third-party database vendors.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Third-Party Collection</span>
          <br>
          Our Service may use Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google, Inc. (“Google”). Google Analytics uses cookies, to help us analyze how users use the Service. You may be able to opt-out of Google’s collection. Please visit Google’s <a class="info-text-link" href="http://google.com/settings/ads/">Ads Preferences Manager</a> or the <a class="info-text-link" href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/">Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on</a> for more information.
          <br>
          <br>
          The Service may also use cookies for its own analytics.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Internal Use of Information by Unlockable</span>
          <br>
          We accept and gather information in an effort to provide you with the Service. This includes the internal use of your information to tailor the Services to your interests and improve the user experience of the Services. Additionally, Unlockable may use your information for administration of the Service, such as for communicating with you about the Services, Unlockable’s associates, or offers from Unlockable and its associates.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Sharing Information with Third-Parties, Consultants, and Affiliates</span>
          <br>
          We may share your information with our consultants and affiliates in order for us to provide you with the Service and to operate Unlockable. For instance, our internet service provider and web host may have access to your data to perform their services for Unlockable. Further, Unlockable may retain third-party consultants to perform analysis on your data and to otherwise provide consulting services to Unlockable that may include review of your data. These types of disclosures will be on a confidential basis.
          <br>
          <br>
          Unlockable may share your Non-Personal Information with our business associates and advertising partners. Such sharing is generally for the purpose of marketing Unlockable’s own services and to discuss and offer Unlockable’s services to advertisers that may wish to participate in the Unlockable platform.
          <br>
          <br>
          In certain identified circumstances, select offers or programs being promoted or offered through Unlockable require the disclosure of your Personal Information to third-party advertisers or business associates. This is generally where Unlockable’s business associate requires this information for eligibility to participate in a program, giveaway or offer. Your participation in such a program is voluntary, and you will be given notice of the sharing of Personal Information in this context.
          <br>
          <br>
          Further, we may disclose collected information to the extent we believe it necessary to comply with the law, such as in response to a subpoena or court order, to defend a legal claim or otherwise as permitted by applicable law. Additionally, we may transfer your information to successor in interest, which may include but may not be limited to a third-party in the event of an acquisition, sale, merger or bankruptcy.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Access and Control</span>
          <br>
          Unlockable may provide you with the ability to access the Personal Information we have collected about you. It is our intention to expand this ability over time. At present, if you would like us to delete your data, please contact us at <a class="info-text-link" href="mailto:privacy@unlockable.com?subject=Account Deletion">privacy@unlockable.com</a> and your request will be taken under advisement.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Links and Integration</span>
          <br>
          Our Service may contain links to other services or may be integrated into the websites or services of third-parties. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of such other sites or services. When you leave our Service to visit another website, application or service, please read such third-party’s privacy statements. This Privacy Policy applies solely to information collected by Unlockable through the Service.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Security</span>
          <br>
          We employ procedural and technical safeguards to secure your personal information against loss, theft, alteration, and unauthorized access, use and disclosure. We also employ security procedures to protect your information from unauthorized access by users inside and outside the company. These measures include password protection, firewalls, encryption and similar methods.
          <br>
          <br>
          Regardless of the precautions taken by Unlockable, No transmission of data over the Internet is guaranteed to be completely secure. It may be possible for third parties not under our control to intercept or access transmissions or private communications unlawfully. While we strive to protect personal information, we cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information you transmit to us.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Children and Privacy</span>
          <br>
          We do not knowingly permit users if they are under 13 years old, and therefore do not request personally identifiable information from anyone under the age of 13. If we become aware that a customer is under the age of 13 and has provided us with personal information without prior verifiable parental consent, we will remove his or her personally identifiable registration information from our files. If you are the parent or guardian of a person under the age of 13 who has provided personally identifiable information to us without your approval, please inform us by contacting us at the e-mail address below.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">California Privacy Rights</span>
          <br>
          California law allows California residents to request information regarding our disclosures in the prior calendar year, if any, of their personally identifiable information to third parties. To make such a request, please contact us at <a class="info-text-link" href="mailto:privacy@unlockable.com?subject=Request for Privacy Info">privacy@unlockable.com</a> with "Request for Privacy Information" in the subject line. Please include enough detail for us to locate your file; at a minimum, your name, email, and username, if any. We will attempt to provide you with the requested information within thirty (30) days of receipt. We reserve our right not to respond to requests sent more than once in a calendar year, or requests submitted to an address other than the one posted in this notice. Please note that this law does not cover all information sharing. Our disclosure only includes information covered by the law.
          <br>
          <br>
          <span class="info-text-title">Contact Information</span>
          <br>
          If you have any questions or suggestions regarding our Privacy Policy, please contact us via e-mail at <a class="info-text-link" href="mailto:privacy@unlockable.com">privacy@unlockable.com</a>. 

